        <h3>NITI Aayog Registration</h3>
        <br>
        <p>NITI stands for National Institution for Transforming India Aayog. This scheme was launched by the Government of India and was introduced in 2015. The main objective was to promote a strong partnership between Non- Government Organizations (NGOs)/Voluntary Organizations (VOs) and the Indian Government.
    <br>
    NITI Aayog has launched an online portal called NGO Darpan. This portal enables NGOs or VOs to register centrally and facilitates in creating a source of information regarding NGOs or VOs, State-wise or Sector-wise. Government of India keeps record of all the registration process through an online database. And all NGOs/VOs are obligated to register under NITI Aayog for receiving grants under various Government programs. In this article, we shall discuss the NITI Aayog NGO Registration in India.</p>
    <br><br>  
    <h3>Benefits Of NITI Aayog Registration</h3>
    <br>
    <ul>
        <li>For Registration of FCRA, a NITI Aayog unique ID is required, but currently, it is not mandatory.</li>
        <li>It increases the credibility of Trust/Society/NGO, which enables them get a general public donation.</li>
        <li>It has been manadated to obtain NITI Aayog NGO Registration to avail of various schemes provided by the Government of India.</li>
        <li>The databases of all the presently active and blacklisted Non-Government Organizations are available and governed with the help of the NGO Darpan Portal.</li>
        <li>Through the NGO Darpan portal, one can directly apply for grants offered by the Government of India. And also stay updated about a lot of other things.</li>
    </ul>
    <br><br>
    <h3>Documents Required For NITI Aayog Registration</h3>
    <br>
    <ol>
        <li>Duly certified copy of the Trust Deed</li>
        <li>Copy of the MOA (Memorandum of Association) of the company</li>
        <li>Copy of the AOA (Articles of Association) of the company
</li>
        <li>Copy of Certificate of Registration of Society</li>
        <li>PAN Card of NGO/VO</li>
        <li>Details on FCRA</li>
        <li>Valid contact information - email, phone number</li>
        <li>Last 5 years details of all source of funds from government agencies</li>
        <li>Aadhar Card and PAN Card of all the members.</li>
        <li>Chairman of Organization and Chief Functionary Details</li>
    </ol>
